WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.560
How does default discrimination happen in a computer system that doesn't even know a

00:00:04.560 --> 00:00:06.080
person's race?

00:00:06.080 --> 00:00:10.700
We usually treat automation as the ultimate solution to human bias, replacing prejudice

00:00:10.700 --> 00:00:12.480
with objective math.

00:00:12.480 --> 00:00:16.640
Take the automated risk assessment tools that judges use to predict if a prospective parolee

00:00:16.640 --> 00:00:18.200
will re-offend.

00:00:18.200 --> 00:00:23.760
The algorithm collects standard, neutral-sounding inputs, like financial history, education,

00:00:23.760 --> 00:00:27.560
and neighborhood characteristics, to generate a numerical risk score.

00:00:27.560 --> 00:00:32.440
The formula explicitly excludes race to stay perfectly colorblind, yet real-world studies

00:00:32.440 --> 00:00:37.760
show these tools falsely flag black defendants as high risk at almost twice the rate of white

00:00:37.760 --> 00:00:38.760
defendants.

00:00:38.760 --> 00:00:39.760
Why?

00:00:39.760 --> 00:00:43.360
Because the calculation relies on a neutral data point that secretly carries the weight

00:00:43.360 --> 00:00:47.200
of historical inequality, a stand-in called a proxy.

00:00:47.200 --> 00:00:49.240
Take neighborhood data, for instance.

00:00:49.240 --> 00:00:53.640
Because certain areas are historically segregated and heavily over-patrolled by police, the

00:00:53.640 --> 00:00:57.320
geographic data itself is already deeply skewed.

00:00:57.320 --> 00:01:01.000
Researchers don't have to write malicious code to automate anti-Blackness, they just

00:01:01.000 --> 00:01:04.880
have to build their tool on top of an already unequal society.

00:01:04.880 --> 00:01:07.240
And that perspective parolee from the beginning?

00:01:07.240 --> 00:01:11.480
The algorithm denies them release, not by predicting their future, but by mathematically

00:01:11.480 --> 00:01:14.080
scoring the historical inequalities of their neighborhood.
